	<p>We offer Home Equity Lines Of Credit (HELOCs) and Home Equity Loans at great terms
	and conditions from	many sources.</p>

	<p>Put your home to work for you. It's a great way
	to utilize the equity in your home to pay off high interest credit card
	debt, finance college education costs or make improvements. Have cash
    at-the-ready without having to go to the time and trouble of talking to
    bankers and filling out more applications with a HELOC. Keep
	in mind that the interest is nearly always tax deductible (see <a
	href="http://www.lightning-mortgage.com/InterestRates/EducationTaxes.htm"
	class="LoanTypes" >Homeowner Tax Advantages</a>).</p>

<div style="float:left; width:48%;text-align:left;padding:0 8px 0 0;">
	<p style="font-size:medium;color:#660033;">Home Equity Installment Loan</p>
	<ul>
	<li>Fixed rate - your payment stays the same for the entire life of your loan</li>
	<li>Fixed Repayment Period - you can choose a term that works for you, such as 5 years,
	10 years, 15 years or 20 years</li>
	<li>One Time Borrowing - good for funding purchases such as vehicles, vacations, weddings,
	or any large one time purchase</li></ul>
</div>
<div style="float:right; width:48%;text-align:left;padding:0 0 0 8px;">
	<p style="font-size:medium;color:#660033;">Home Equity Line of Credit</p>
	<ul>
	<li>Variable Rate - your interest rate varies over the life of your loan</li>
	<li>Revolving Repayment Period - as you pay off your loan,
	you can re-borrow up to your credit limit as easily as writing a check</li>
	<li>Continuous Borrowing - good for funding ongoing purchases,
	such as home remodeling projects or college expenses</li></ul>
</div>
